03:03.520 --> 03:08.520
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00ff00>elderman</font> ==

03:11.042 --> 04:25.521
[♪]

04:31.388 --> 04:33.122
<i>PHYSICIAN:</i>
<i>Come with me! Hurry!</i>

04:33.190 --> 04:35.624
[door banging open]

04:35.692 --> 04:36.992
[panting]

04:37.060 --> 04:38.594
<i>CESARE:</i>
<i>Help!</i>

04:38.661 --> 04:39.995
<i>Father!</i>

04:43.266 --> 04:44.733
<i>MAN:</i>
<i>Summon the physician!</i>

04:44.801 --> 04:46.802
<i>MAN:</i>
<i>Is he dead?</i>

04:46.903 --> 04:50.072
[loud clatter]

04:50.139 --> 04:58.447
[♪]

04:58.548 --> 05:03.152
<i>[distant bells tolling]</i>

05:03.220 --> 05:05.354
Stand back!

05:05.455 --> 05:07.223
[panting]

05:07.291 --> 05:08.891
<i>GUARD:</i>
<i>Make way, I say!</i>

05:08.959 --> 05:10.159
<i>MAN:</i>
<i>Physician, hurry!</i>

05:10.227 --> 05:11.727
<i>Make way!</i>

05:12.796 --> 05:14.363
Move!
Move aside!

05:14.431 --> 05:15.965
<i>CAPTAIN:</i>
<i>Seal the city!</i>

05:16.032 --> 05:18.166
<i>Close the gates!</i>

05:21.837 --> 05:24.072
[gates slamming]

05:24.139 --> 05:26.273
Make way!
Make way, make way.

05:27.342 --> 05:28.509
Cantarella.

05:28.576 --> 05:30.077
What can you do?

05:31.580 --> 05:32.981
<i>PHYSICIAN:</i>
<i>Nothing.</i>

05:33.048 --> 05:34.982
<i>His soul is already</i>
<i>departing this world.</i>

05:35.050 --> 05:37.018
His soul does not depart
until I give it leave!

05:37.086 --> 05:39.354
But-there is nothing-there
is no remedy, no antidote-

05:39.455 --> 05:41.089
there is nothing to
cure such a case.

05:41.157 --> 05:42.324
<i>LUCREZIA:</i>
<i>No, there is.</i>

05:42.392 --> 05:43.692
<i>There is something -</i>
<i>charcoal.</i>

05:43.760 --> 05:45.828
But I have only read of it,
never seen it done.

05:45.929 --> 05:47.997
I need water, water.

05:48.065 --> 05:49.699
Open his mouth.

05:52.003 --> 05:54.471
[indistinct chatter]

05:59.143 --> 06:00.544
Get this down.

06:03.648 --> 06:05.450
Come on!
Help me!

06:07.886 --> 06:09.587
Force it in until
he can bear no more.

06:09.655 --> 06:11.723
And if he vomits, force more.
You understand me?

06:11.824 --> 06:14.158
But, this is witchcraft.

06:14.226 --> 06:16.194
This is physick!

06:16.262 --> 06:18.163
Get to it!
CESARE: Do what she says.

06:18.230 --> 06:19.197
Every detail.

06:19.265 --> 06:20.798
<i>And, if his soul departs,</i>

06:20.866 --> 06:22.467
I shall ensure it
does not do so alone.

06:22.534 --> 06:23.735
<i>PHYSICIAN:</i>
<i>Yes, Eminence.</i>

06:23.836 --> 06:25.103
Hand me water.

06:25.170 --> 06:26.570
<i>LUCREZIA: Push this</i>
<i>down his throat!</i>

06:26.572 --> 06:28.052
<i>CAPTAIN: Get these</i>
<i>people out of here.</i>

06:28.107 --> 06:29.574
I want this room clear.

06:29.642 --> 06:30.742
<i>CARDINAL:</i>
<i>Ave Maria.</i>

06:30.810 --> 06:32.110
<i>Gratia plena.</i>

06:32.178 --> 06:33.578
<i>Dominus tecum...</i>

06:33.646 --> 06:35.346
LUCREZIA:
Get it down!

06:35.414 --> 06:38.917
<i>...benedictus fructus</i>
<i>ventris tui, Iesus.</i>

06:38.985 --> 06:40.819
<i>ALPHONSO:</i>
<i>Will he live?</i>

06:40.886 --> 06:43.321
<i>CARDINAL: Pater noster, qui</i>
<i>es in caelis, sanctificetur -</i>

06:43.389 --> 06:45.491
I found this
in the boy's cell.

06:47.160 --> 06:50.361
A Dominican salter
in a Franciscan cell?

06:50.429 --> 06:52.630
CARDINAL SFORZA:
I have closed the city.

06:57.502 --> 07:00.271
I must leave.
Do what you can.

07:02.340 --> 07:03.374
Hah!

07:05.510 --> 07:06.944
Yah!

07:08.814 --> 07:10.481
LUCREZIA:
Keep going.

07:11.450 --> 07:12.750
Come on.

07:12.818 --> 07:15.419
The last words
I spoke to him...

07:15.487 --> 07:17.188
Shh...
They tore him apart.

07:17.255 --> 07:18.655
Shh!

07:18.723 --> 07:20.654
It's not yet too late.

07:20.722 --> 07:24.391
<i>[banging on door]</i>

07:24.459 --> 07:25.959
Who's there, Brother?

07:28.095 --> 07:29.462
[gasps in pain]

07:29.530 --> 07:31.230
<i>MONK: Stop!</i>
<i>This is the house of God.</i>

07:31.331 --> 07:33.399
And God is angry.

07:35.168 --> 07:36.735
[grunting]

07:36.803 --> 07:38.103
Ah!

07:38.171 --> 07:40.206
[grunting]

07:41.642 --> 07:42.842
Ah!

07:45.079 --> 07:46.479
Ah!

07:48.000 --> 07:54.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

07:55.989 --> 07:57.790
[pained grunts]

07:57.858 --> 07:59.992
<i>CESARE:</i>
<i>Whose room is this?</i>

08:00.060 --> 08:01.460
<i>MONK:</i>
<i>Cardinal Della Rovere's.</i>

08:01.561 --> 08:03.029
[gasps]
Where is he?

08:03.096 --> 08:05.131
<i>Where is Della Rovere?</i>

08:05.232 --> 08:07.233
My lord.
Cantarella.

08:07.334 --> 08:09.568
You, where he is?

08:09.636 --> 08:11.871
Tell me where you have
hidden Della Rovere-

08:11.938 --> 08:13.306
or your life is forfeit.

08:14.742 --> 08:15.875
[whimpering]

08:17.378 --> 08:20.313
Show me - or I will
gut you like a fish.

08:20.414 --> 08:22.015
You threaten me?

08:22.083 --> 08:23.583
We are men of God!

08:23.651 --> 08:25.218
Men of God who have conspired
to murder my father.

08:25.319 --> 08:26.586
Your father.

08:28.522 --> 08:30.657
CESARE: Did you really think
I would not find you out?

08:30.725 --> 08:32.359
Look at me.

08:32.427 --> 08:33.960
[shouts]
Look at me!

08:36.698 --> 08:38.332
Show me.

08:40.635 --> 08:42.135
Show him.

08:43.605 --> 08:44.872
<i>Get up!</i>

08:47.543 --> 08:51.879
[breathing heavily]

08:51.947 --> 08:54.415
[women quietly weeping]

08:57.619 --> 08:59.886
There is nothing
more I know to do.

09:02.457 --> 09:04.157
Well, we cannot
leave him here.

09:05.326 --> 09:06.694
Come.

09:18.441 --> 09:19.808
We've lost him.

09:22.345 --> 09:24.413
Ah!

09:24.481 --> 09:25.781
Ahh!

09:32.555 --> 09:33.822
<i>CARDINAL COLONNA: [whispering]</i>
<i>It seems our prayers</i>

09:33.923 --> 09:35.858
<i>may not be answered.</i>

09:35.926 --> 09:37.093
<i>CARDINAL SFORZA: [whispering]</i>
<i>That would depend</i>

09:37.160 --> 09:38.461
<i>on the nature</i>
<i>of your prayers.</i>

09:38.528 --> 09:40.729
COLONNA: [whispering]
God forbid he should die.

09:40.830 --> 09:43.499
But should he die...

09:43.567 --> 09:46.602
There will
be opportunity.

09:46.670 --> 09:48.404
There will be mayhem.

09:48.472 --> 09:50.039
CARDINAL DE LUCA:
God wants an Italian.

09:50.107 --> 09:51.841
The Holy Spirit
wants a Roman.

09:51.909 --> 09:53.142
We should decide
amongst ourselves.

09:53.210 --> 09:54.811
Find the safest pair
of Italian hands

09:54.878 --> 09:57.246
and bless the martyr who
brought about this outcome.

09:57.314 --> 09:58.681
<i>COLONNA:</i>
<i>A Roman.</i>

09:58.749 --> 10:00.984
<i>One of the great</i>
<i>Italian families.</i>

10:01.051 --> 10:02.685
<i>CARDINAL VERSUCCI:</i>
<i>Colonna, De Luca,</i>

10:02.753 --> 10:04.920
Piccolimini,
Sforza, Versucci...

10:04.988 --> 10:07.156
Orsini.
Yes.

10:07.224 --> 10:08.891
[chuckles]

10:13.363 --> 10:17.099
[♪]

10:22.606 --> 10:25.107
He could be anywhere.

10:25.175 --> 10:35.751
[♪]

10:35.753 --> 10:43.192
[♪]

10:43.294 --> 10:45.662
His arm, lift his arm.

10:45.729 --> 10:47.664
[♪]

10:47.732 --> 10:49.966
[murmuring]

10:50.034 --> 10:51.502
DELUCA:
Of course.

10:51.569 --> 10:53.837
ORSINI: I would need to know
where you consider me.

10:53.905 --> 10:55.572
DELLA ROVERE:
Cardinal Orsini.

10:55.640 --> 10:57.475
Cardinal DeLuca.

10:57.576 --> 10:59.744
Cardinal Colonna.

10:59.812 --> 11:01.713
Cardinal Sforza.

11:01.780 --> 11:04.015
My brothers; I came
as soon as I heard.

11:04.083 --> 11:05.550
As soon as you heard.

11:05.651 --> 11:07.285
Of the pope's death.

11:07.386 --> 11:08.753
Cardinal Della Rovere,

11:08.821 --> 11:10.755
your information somewhat
pre-empts the matter.

11:14.260 --> 11:15.727
He lives?

11:15.795 --> 11:19.766
PRIEST: In nomine Patri et Filii
et Spiritus Sancti, amen.

11:19.867 --> 11:21.736
PRIEST:
Amen.

11:21.804 --> 11:24.372
PHYSICIAN: The life has
not left him yet, Eminence.

11:24.440 --> 11:27.542
[whispering continues]

11:41.090 --> 11:50.400
[♪]

11:50.402 --> 11:58.008
[♪]

12:02.513 --> 12:03.780
Cesare!

12:05.916 --> 12:07.450
You!

12:07.518 --> 12:09.319
Your blade! Cesare!
Put up your blade!

12:09.387 --> 12:11.288
<i>CARDINALS:</i>
<i>No, no, no!</i>

12:12.857 --> 12:14.391
Cesare!

12:17.862 --> 12:21.399
The least disturbance
may tip the balance.

12:34.046 --> 12:35.613
[relieved sigh]

12:53.530 --> 12:55.164
Cesare-please!

12:55.232 --> 12:56.165
Now think!

12:56.233 --> 12:57.433
Think of what?

12:57.501 --> 12:59.335
Of what happens next.

13:02.272 --> 13:05.608
Of what becomes of us
if he dies.

13:05.709 --> 13:07.810
You, me, Lucrezia.

13:09.412 --> 13:12.047
Do you think we've
made friends here?

13:12.115 --> 13:14.583
Do you think we can
turn to our allies?

13:14.651 --> 13:16.252
Where are these
allies, Cesare?

13:16.319 --> 13:17.920
Who are our friends?

13:17.988 --> 13:21.324
I'm not pope.
Neither are you.

13:21.392 --> 13:24.160
Without him,
what becomes of us?

13:24.261 --> 13:26.162
Will he die?

13:26.263 --> 13:28.531
It hangs in
the balance.

13:28.598 --> 13:32.234
Then we must wait to see
which way the balance falls.

13:32.302 --> 13:35.271
Meanwhile, look to me
for your safety.

13:43.979 --> 13:46.181
<i>PICCOLOMINI: We should</i>
<i>align ourselves now</i>

13:46.248 --> 13:49.384
<i>to reap what we can.</i>

13:49.451 --> 13:51.352
<i>VERSUCCI:</i>
<i>There's nothing else.</i>

13:51.420 --> 13:54.088
<i>ORSINI:</i>
<i>There are the Borgia estates.</i>

13:54.156 --> 13:56.357
<i>PICCOLOMINI:</i>
<i>Are we agreed?</i>

13:56.458 --> 13:58.593
<i>An Italian then?</i>

13:58.660 --> 14:00.294
<i>ORSINI:</i>
<i>And a Roman.</i>

14:00.362 --> 14:02.163
<i>VERSUCCI:</i>
<i>Della Rovere is both.</i>

14:02.231 --> 14:03.931
<i>He has been long</i>
<i>in the wilderness.</i>

14:03.999 --> 14:05.366
<i>ORSINI:</i>
<i>For far too long.</i>

14:05.434 --> 14:08.202
How long will
any of the Borgias

14:08.270 --> 14:12.106
survive once
he's gone?

14:12.207 --> 14:14.075
I want the treasury.

14:14.176 --> 14:15.543
And I want land.

14:20.082 --> 14:21.716
SFORZA:
In nomini Patri...

14:21.784 --> 14:31.092
[praying]

14:31.160 --> 14:33.995
[baby crying]

14:34.062 --> 14:36.898
Sh, sh, sh.
<i>[bell tolling]</i>

14:36.965 --> 14:39.701
Sh, sh, sh.

14:39.768 --> 14:44.172
[crying continues]

14:44.240 --> 14:45.106
<i>He won't sleep.</i>

14:45.207 --> 14:46.741
Take him back to the villa.

14:46.809 --> 14:48.476
Put him in his bed there.

14:48.543 --> 14:51.078
We'll join you as soon as we
know his grandfather's fate.

14:51.146 --> 14:52.479
Thank you.

14:52.547 --> 14:54.181
[crying continues]

14:54.249 --> 14:56.617
Shh...

14:56.685 --> 14:57.818
Be safe.

14:57.886 --> 14:59.286
Yes, my lady.

15:07.629 --> 15:09.430
You should go too.
It's not safe here.

15:09.498 --> 15:11.265
If it's not safe for me,
how can it be safe for you?

15:11.333 --> 15:12.533
It's not.

15:12.601 --> 15:14.002
But I am a Borgia,
and my place is here.

15:14.069 --> 15:15.837
ALFONSO
I'm to be your husband -

15:15.905 --> 15:17.672
LUCREZIA:
Yes, but you are not yet.

15:17.740 --> 15:20.642
Go back to your villa and...

15:20.709 --> 15:24.945
When this is over -
one way or the other -

15:25.013 --> 15:26.947
I will send for you,
never fear.

15:29.751 --> 15:32.386
I would protect you,
you know.

15:32.454 --> 15:33.855
The time may come.

15:33.923 --> 15:35.557
But not now.

15:43.232 --> 15:45.132
[sighs]

15:49.071 --> 15:50.538
VANOZZA:
The Lord is with thee.

15:50.606 --> 15:51.872
Blessed art thou
amongst women,

15:51.940 --> 15:53.407
and blessed is the fruit
of thy womb, Jesus.

15:53.475 --> 15:56.210
Holy Mary, Mother of God,
Pray for us sinners...

15:56.278 --> 16:00.581
[whispering prayers]

16:05.655 --> 16:19.101
[♪]

16:19.103 --> 16:24.773
[♪]

16:24.775 --> 16:32.247
[♪]

16:32.315 --> 16:34.183
<i>[soldiers shouting]</i>

16:34.250 --> 16:35.717
<i>CAPTAIN:</i>
<i>Take position!</i>

16:35.785 --> 16:37.419
<i>SOLDIER:</i>
<i>In place!</i>

16:40.623 --> 16:42.324
<i>CAPTAIN:</i>
<i>Papal guard!</i>

16:44.061 --> 16:47.597
Cardinal...

16:47.664 --> 16:50.234
Tell me-
um...

16:50.302 --> 16:53.604
Where are the lines
of allegiance?

16:53.705 --> 16:54.972
Hmm?

16:55.073 --> 16:56.340
[scoffs]
Please...

16:56.408 --> 16:58.209
Do not tell me that my
father did not have you

16:58.276 --> 17:01.045
with your ear pressed
to the wall on such matters.

17:01.113 --> 17:03.347
I wish to know.

17:03.415 --> 17:07.050
Which cardinals owe favours
to which other cardinals?

17:07.117 --> 17:09.686
Who is in whose pocket?
Who seeks the papacy?

17:09.755 --> 17:12.923
And who merely
wishes an easy life?

17:12.991 --> 17:15.893
You know all this,
do you not?

17:15.960 --> 17:18.762
Yes, your father
encouraged me to, uh...

17:18.829 --> 17:20.864
...to know all of this.

17:20.932 --> 17:23.166
And?

17:23.233 --> 17:26.336
I have a list in
my private apartments.

17:26.436 --> 17:28.339
Names and notes.

17:29.241 --> 17:31.075
CESARE:
Get it.

17:41.353 --> 17:43.988
[door closing]

17:44.089 --> 17:46.091
[floorboard creaking]

17:47.660 --> 17:50.162
Did my cousin
Catherina send you?

17:52.131 --> 17:54.433
You are not welcome here.

17:54.533 --> 17:55.967
This is a dagger's tip

17:56.035 --> 17:58.303
upon which all events turn,
Cardinal.

17:58.371 --> 18:00.905
We are at the fork
in the road.

18:00.973 --> 18:03.908
Rome must not be allowed
to take the wrong path here.

18:07.078 --> 18:08.512
Did you do this?

18:08.580 --> 18:09.980
No.

18:10.048 --> 18:11.848
It took us by surprise.

18:11.916 --> 18:14.718
But it was our intention,
at the proper moment.

18:14.785 --> 18:17.654
Preparations have been
made for some time now,

18:17.722 --> 18:21.759
certain...
matters arranged.

18:21.827 --> 18:23.460
All this has done
is move things along

18:23.561 --> 18:26.230
a little faster than
we'd anticipated.

18:26.298 --> 18:29.466
You have always known this
day would come, Ascanio.

18:31.236 --> 18:33.037
All that has
changed is that now

18:33.104 --> 18:35.038
I require your
assistance in the matter.

18:35.106 --> 18:38.508
By what right dare you
require anything of me?

18:38.576 --> 18:40.544
By right of blood.
Of family.

18:40.645 --> 18:42.145
Of kinsmen.

18:42.213 --> 18:43.981
And by right of what
is good for Rome.

18:44.049 --> 18:45.449
And if I refuse?

18:45.517 --> 18:47.518
You should not refuse.

18:54.493 --> 18:55.560
If he dies -

18:55.628 --> 18:57.896
When he dies.

18:57.964 --> 19:01.533
What comes after?

19:01.600 --> 19:03.868
Are you here to dangle the
Papacy of Rome in front of me

19:03.936 --> 19:06.637
like a carrot in front
of a hungry mule?

19:06.705 --> 19:08.839
[snickers]

19:08.907 --> 19:11.709
Are you saying you would
refuse, if it were offered?

19:18.249 --> 19:21.584
Understand me clearly.

19:21.652 --> 19:26.256
Your cousin Catherina will
not be denied this chance.

19:26.323 --> 19:27.890
He will die.

19:29.927 --> 19:32.628
[quietly]
As will they all die.

19:34.431 --> 19:36.098
All?

19:36.166 --> 19:38.935
The whole brood of
bastards die tonight.

19:39.002 --> 19:40.336
So you should
give thought

19:40.404 --> 19:42.972
to where you want
to be come the dawn.

19:43.040 --> 19:45.942
One step closer to
the throne of Rome,

19:46.009 --> 19:47.643
or confronting a pope

19:47.711 --> 19:50.379
whose family just died
at Sforza hands.

19:52.916 --> 19:54.983
Come home, Ascanio.

19:55.051 --> 19:57.118
You have been
too long away.

20:11.633 --> 20:16.203
[Cardinals murmuring]

20:21.709 --> 20:23.276
DELLA ROVERE: [whispering]
It would be good

20:23.344 --> 20:25.111
if we could
count on your support.

20:25.212 --> 20:27.113
Of course.

20:27.181 --> 20:28.748
Thank you.

20:34.254 --> 20:37.390
You believe that one of you
can beat him.

20:37.491 --> 20:40.059
You can't.

20:40.127 --> 20:43.863
Sforza knows too well your
strengths and weaknesses,

20:43.931 --> 20:46.266
<i>your little corridor politics.</i>

20:46.333 --> 20:48.134
He'll set you
against one another,

20:48.202 --> 20:50.570
let you vie for position,

20:50.637 --> 20:54.040
and then take down the winner
without breaking a sweat.

20:54.141 --> 20:56.175
I can beat him -

20:56.243 --> 20:58.344
if you lend
your strength to mine.

20:58.412 --> 21:00.013
None of you wants to
be pope in any case.

21:00.080 --> 21:01.514
What you want is power.

21:01.615 --> 21:03.316
And that I will give you,

21:03.384 --> 21:04.884
all that you
could eat of it.

21:04.952 --> 21:08.155
[Alexander gasps]
Your Holiness!

21:08.223 --> 21:09.690
CESARE: Water!
Dottore, water, now!

21:09.791 --> 21:10.791
Yes, my lord!

21:10.892 --> 21:13.760
Oh!

21:13.828 --> 21:15.395
Your Holiness!

21:19.233 --> 21:20.866
[vomiting]

21:20.968 --> 21:22.702
[coughing]

21:22.769 --> 21:24.770
[murmuring]

21:26.839 --> 21:28.506
[gasping]

21:28.608 --> 21:30.141
[sigh]

21:35.782 --> 21:38.517
CARDINALS: Gloria Patri,
et Filio, et Spiritui Sancto.

21:38.585 --> 21:42.654
Sicut erat in principio,
et nunc, et semper,

21:42.722 --> 21:44.890
et in saecula
saeculorum.

21:44.991 --> 21:46.892
Amen.

21:49.863 --> 21:54.233
[moaning hoarsely]

21:55.402 --> 21:58.972
<i>CARDINALS: Gloria Patri,</i>
<i>et Filio, et Spiritui Sancto.</i>

21:59.040 --> 22:12.554
[♪]

22:12.556 --> 22:25.568
[♪]

22:25.570 --> 22:33.443
[♪]

22:37.048 --> 22:40.083
Your place is in
the Vatican, Cardinal.

22:50.894 --> 22:53.096
Rodrigo.

22:55.065 --> 22:56.265
[sighs]

22:59.369 --> 23:00.803
CESARE:
You can leave us.

23:03.474 --> 23:04.441
I...

23:04.508 --> 23:06.877
Shh...
Don't try to speak.

23:06.945 --> 23:09.079
Your throat will be
torn from the charcoal.

23:12.183 --> 23:13.651
It's safe.
[gasps]

23:13.719 --> 23:15.920
It's safe,
it's safe.

23:23.496 --> 23:24.830
[sigh]

23:28.235 --> 23:31.203
I saw the face of death.

23:31.271 --> 23:33.205
<i>CESARE: Well,</i>
<i>you're not dead, Father.</i>

23:33.273 --> 23:34.741
<i>You live.</i>

23:34.842 --> 23:37.110
For how long?

23:37.211 --> 23:39.212
A day and a night.

23:42.616 --> 23:43.849
By who?

23:43.917 --> 23:45.784
Della Rovere.

23:45.852 --> 23:48.921
<i>The Dominicans were hiding</i>
<i>him right here in Rome.</i>

23:50.891 --> 23:54.060
But we have him

23:54.128 --> 23:56.997
and I will know
how many others,

23:57.064 --> 23:58.665
their names,

23:58.733 --> 24:01.568
<i>their families...</i>

24:01.636 --> 24:05.305
He will tell everything
before I'm done with him,

24:05.373 --> 24:07.308
and then he will
beg for death.

24:09.478 --> 24:14.815
They settled like
crows around me...

24:14.883 --> 24:18.653
I heard them...

24:18.721 --> 24:23.024
...praying
for my death.

24:23.092 --> 24:24.860
[mutters]
I heard them.

24:26.129 --> 24:27.396
They're gone now.

24:29.032 --> 24:31.366
I have disappointed them.

24:35.805 --> 24:37.739
How come I did not die?

24:37.807 --> 24:39.574
You owe your life
to Lucrezia.

24:41.411 --> 24:43.645
And the grace of God.

24:43.713 --> 24:45.413
Yes, and that.

24:45.514 --> 24:48.149
No, not God.

24:48.250 --> 24:49.784
Ah...

24:49.852 --> 24:52.920
[sighs]

24:52.987 --> 24:55.589
Where is he?

24:55.690 --> 24:57.590
Who, Father?

24:57.658 --> 24:59.659
Juan.
Where is Juan?

25:10.937 --> 25:12.638
[sighs]

25:12.706 --> 25:14.240
[whimpers]
Juan.

25:16.510 --> 25:17.878
[sighs]

25:17.946 --> 25:19.380
Look at me.

25:19.448 --> 25:21.049
<i>Look at me.</i>

25:21.150 --> 25:23.318
<i>You have us.</i>

25:23.386 --> 25:25.654
<i>We are here.</i>

25:25.722 --> 25:27.522
<i>ALEXANDER:</i>
<i>One day and a night.</i>

25:31.594 --> 25:34.696
So much has changed.

25:34.764 --> 25:36.364
[door creaking open]

25:39.068 --> 25:40.401
Ah!

25:44.206 --> 25:45.840
<i>[door slamming shut]</i>

25:57.953 --> 26:05.426
[weeping]

26:11.032 --> 26:14.535
[indistinct conversations]

26:14.602 --> 26:16.336
[birds chirping;
water flowing]

26:16.438 --> 26:18.606
[indistinct conversations]

26:46.201 --> 26:50.304
<i>[vendors calling out]</i>

26:50.372 --> 26:53.707
<i>[indistinct</i>
<i>conversations throughout]</i>

27:05.286 --> 27:06.619
Well?

27:06.720 --> 27:09.089
What of my family?

27:12.026 --> 27:13.827
<i>Make way!</i>

27:13.894 --> 27:15.862
They're well, so far.

27:15.930 --> 27:22.168
And whether they remain so
depends on your answer.

27:22.236 --> 27:24.070
There are five guards
inside the villa.

27:24.138 --> 27:25.972
I don't know how many outside.

27:26.039 --> 27:27.173
Where placed?

27:27.274 --> 27:29.275
The main doors.
Two in the garden.

27:29.343 --> 27:31.644
The others move around,
upstairs mostly.

27:31.745 --> 27:33.446
I'm not sure of more.

27:35.916 --> 27:38.017
That's good enough.

27:38.118 --> 27:40.353
And the family?

27:40.421 --> 27:42.655
They will return when
the pope is well.

27:42.723 --> 27:44.925
Or when he dies.

27:47.128 --> 27:50.097
The window in the washing
room leads outside?

27:52.233 --> 27:54.334
When the family returns,

27:54.402 --> 27:57.537
leave the window
unlatched and walk away.

27:57.605 --> 27:59.740
But you must promise me -

27:59.807 --> 28:02.209
Please, spare the child.
He has done nothing.

28:03.778 --> 28:04.912
Of course.

28:04.979 --> 28:07.114
You have my word.

28:07.215 --> 28:09.015
No harm to the child.

28:17.324 --> 28:18.924
Let's go.

28:21.695 --> 28:25.564
[roosters squawking]
[men cheering, laughing]

28:25.665 --> 28:31.035
[indistinct shouts]

28:31.103 --> 28:32.270
MAN:
Okay, go ahead!

28:32.338 --> 28:36.108
Yeah, yeah, yeah!
That's it! Go!

28:36.176 --> 28:38.210
Hit him!
Hit him!

28:39.312 --> 28:41.380
<i>Peck his eyes out!</i>

28:41.481 --> 28:43.115
Yeah! Get him!
Yeah, that's it!

28:43.183 --> 28:44.383
Call it off.

28:44.484 --> 28:46.118
What's happened?

28:46.186 --> 28:47.587
He's alive!

28:49.490 --> 28:51.491
[squawking]

28:51.559 --> 28:53.293
You're certain?

28:53.361 --> 28:54.995
When I left he was
calling for water.

28:55.063 --> 28:56.597
By now he's probably
fucking some servant girl

28:56.665 --> 28:59.200
with a wine jug in one hand
and a swan's leg in the other.

28:59.301 --> 29:01.035
It's over.

29:01.136 --> 29:02.770
Don't be a fool.

29:02.871 --> 29:05.106
Are you deaf?
He's alive.

29:05.173 --> 29:07.040
So make him die.

29:07.108 --> 29:09.476
The others die
tonight in any case.

29:09.577 --> 29:12.412
I've already given the word.

29:12.514 --> 29:14.848
Dear God.

29:14.916 --> 29:17.584
There's no backing
down now.

29:17.652 --> 29:22.122
Within the month Rome
will have a new pope.

29:22.189 --> 29:24.858
Better for all that it is a
man of moderation and wisdom

29:24.926 --> 29:28.229
such as yourself.

29:28.297 --> 29:29.931
You're insane.

29:29.998 --> 29:32.033
[scoffs]

29:32.100 --> 29:33.868
He trusts you.

29:35.905 --> 29:37.940
Toledo steel.

29:39.609 --> 29:41.677
It's one of a pair.

29:44.014 --> 29:45.848
What have you done
with the other?

29:49.720 --> 29:52.054
I told you, preparations
had been made.

29:54.491 --> 29:57.326
In the pope's chamber.

29:57.394 --> 30:01.330
Concealed in the crucifix
upon his offering table.

30:04.100 --> 30:06.035
[whispers]
You know what to do.

30:07.304 --> 30:09.706
[door creaking open]

30:18.482 --> 30:21.050
My father lives.

30:21.118 --> 30:22.351
You've failed.

30:22.453 --> 30:24.053
Ah...

30:24.155 --> 30:26.890
What say you to that?

30:26.957 --> 30:29.625
Today he lives.

30:29.726 --> 30:31.827
One day he will not.

30:31.895 --> 30:33.696
And on that day,
where will you be?

30:36.733 --> 30:39.768
You do know what
awaits you, hmm?

30:42.805 --> 30:46.341
What we did
to Savonarola

30:46.408 --> 30:48.876
will seem like
the merest whimsy

30:48.944 --> 30:51.446
compared to what
I will inflict on you.

30:54.150 --> 30:55.717
Wait...

30:56.752 --> 30:58.820
What I said, I meant.

30:58.921 --> 31:00.889
Give thought to it.

31:00.957 --> 31:03.158
Where will you be
when he's gone?

31:04.527 --> 31:08.497
They will tear you
down like jackals.

31:08.564 --> 31:09.631
I can help you.

31:09.732 --> 31:10.999
I have no need of your help.

31:11.100 --> 31:12.534
I can pave the way.

31:12.602 --> 31:15.004
Every word from
your lips is a lie.

31:15.071 --> 31:18.541
I'm beaten.
I have failed.

31:18.608 --> 31:20.809
I know that.

31:20.877 --> 31:22.978
What use am I
to you dead?

31:23.079 --> 31:25.080
[snickers]

31:25.148 --> 31:27.415
I do not mean for
you to be dead.

31:31.453 --> 31:34.989
Not for a long, long time.

31:35.057 --> 31:36.457
[knocks on door]

31:45.101 --> 31:46.701
[sighs]

31:49.805 --> 31:51.740
I saw the face of death.

31:51.807 --> 31:54.643
I know.
You said.

31:54.710 --> 31:57.446
And I was afraid.

31:57.513 --> 31:59.748
I am so afraid.

31:59.815 --> 32:01.950
Don't be.

32:02.017 --> 32:03.384
It would take more
than cantarella

32:03.485 --> 32:05.086
to fell an ox like you.

32:05.153 --> 32:07.355
No, you don't understand.

32:13.930 --> 32:15.998
I didn't see
the face of God.

32:21.004 --> 32:22.939
He was not there.

32:25.743 --> 32:28.178
Why did He not
show Himself to me?

32:30.581 --> 32:33.550
But I heard the others.

32:33.618 --> 32:36.386
I heard them.

32:36.454 --> 32:38.922
Colonna.
Versucci.

32:38.989 --> 32:42.759
DeLuca,
Della Rovere.

32:42.860 --> 32:47.297
How they prayed
for my death,

32:47.365 --> 32:49.733
and swore to
see me buried

32:49.801 --> 32:54.405
and never again a Spaniard
on the papal throne.

32:57.810 --> 33:01.413
Carrion crows pecking away.

33:01.480 --> 33:04.750
And where was God
to protect me?

33:05.852 --> 33:07.686
You must rest.

33:07.753 --> 33:10.488
Now close your eyes
and sleep.

33:15.995 --> 33:17.796
[whispers]
He sleeps?

33:17.864 --> 33:21.233
He frets,
as if in fever.

33:21.334 --> 33:23.468
You've done
such work today.

33:23.536 --> 33:26.204
Take mother home.
Stay with her.

33:26.272 --> 33:28.139
Take some sleep
for tomorrow.

33:28.207 --> 33:30.509
I'll stay with him.

33:30.576 --> 33:32.844
Look after him.

33:48.461 --> 33:50.028
[groans]

33:50.129 --> 33:53.332
I heard that voice.

33:57.003 --> 33:59.872
In the room, before
the poison took hold

33:59.940 --> 34:02.408
and darkness
dragged me down.

34:06.045 --> 34:10.147
I heard you
call out to me.

34:10.248 --> 34:14.318
"Father, Father."

34:16.588 --> 34:19.657
And you held me
in your hands.

34:22.092 --> 34:23.694
Come here.
Come.

34:42.683 --> 34:45.619
There was something
before the darkness.

34:49.424 --> 34:54.161
Something you said,
something you told me...

34:56.231 --> 34:59.900
...that the world
must never know.

34:59.968 --> 35:07.175
Your brother's murder
was a terrible crime,

35:09.878 --> 35:15.617
and every crime must be
seen to have a punishment.

35:18.587 --> 35:25.427
So we must find the person
who is to be punished.

35:28.032 --> 35:30.734
You understand?

35:35.507 --> 35:37.241
And I?

35:39.110 --> 35:42.146
You have to find
your own peace.

36:04.136 --> 36:05.837
[sigh]

36:07.273 --> 36:11.210
[indistinct
conversations throughout]

36:11.311 --> 36:24.756
[♪]

36:24.758 --> 36:32.998
[♪]

36:33.066 --> 36:34.834
<i>CAPTAIN:</i>
<i>Papal guard!</i>

36:36.036 --> 36:37.670
<i>Forward!</i>

36:43.243 --> 36:44.944
<i>ORSINI: I will speak</i>
<i>with the prisoner.</i>

36:45.011 --> 36:46.771
<i>You are relieved.</i>
<i>GUARDS: Yes, Your Eminence.</i>

36:50.683 --> 36:52.717
What is this?
This is your freedom.

36:52.785 --> 36:54.486
Don't forget who put
it in your hands.

36:54.553 --> 36:56.154
But why?

36:57.356 --> 36:59.590
Others may succeed where you have not.
[screaming, gasping]

36:59.658 --> 37:02.492
And then, Rome will
have need of you.

37:02.560 --> 37:04.194
Guard.

37:05.330 --> 37:08.165
I will not forget this.

37:08.232 --> 37:11.234
Go with them.
They will show you the way.

37:11.302 --> 37:13.203
God be with you.
And with you.

37:27.685 --> 37:29.052
[guard stomps]

37:31.422 --> 37:33.623
SFORZA:
Is this necessary?

37:33.691 --> 37:36.559
My Lord Cesare's
orders.

37:51.443 --> 37:53.243
No...

37:54.912 --> 37:56.513
[shouts]
Guards!

38:02.954 --> 38:05.056
[unlatching window]

38:08.494 --> 38:10.429
Della Rovere!
Find him!

38:11.497 --> 38:12.798
Follow me!
Yes, my lord!

38:12.899 --> 38:14.599
Search everywhere!

38:43.296 --> 38:44.797
[steel scrapes scabbard]

38:53.873 --> 38:56.308
<i>[baby crying]</i>

38:59.945 --> 39:01.613
Oh!
You scared me.

39:06.452 --> 39:08.086
What is it?

39:08.187 --> 39:10.155
Do you not hear
the child crying?

39:15.327 --> 39:16.995
[gasps]

39:18.297 --> 39:19.998
Look at me.

39:21.633 --> 39:23.267
I said, look at me.

39:24.737 --> 39:27.072
I had no choice.

39:27.139 --> 39:29.541
Hm.
You had every choice.

39:29.642 --> 39:31.609
[struggling]

39:45.658 --> 39:46.991
[pebble hitting floor]

39:50.095 --> 39:51.729
[stifled shout]

40:12.017 --> 40:14.785
[panting]

40:14.853 --> 40:16.621
Della Rovere is free.

40:17.790 --> 40:18.823
What?

40:18.891 --> 40:20.458
There are dead men

40:20.526 --> 40:22.727
strewn through
my father's house

40:22.828 --> 40:25.096
and Della Rovere is free.

40:25.197 --> 40:27.098
All is well here?

40:30.502 --> 40:32.536
No...

40:32.604 --> 40:35.105
No, all is not
well here.

40:36.541 --> 40:38.576
Just tell me.

40:41.880 --> 40:44.983
There is a plot
to kill your family.

40:45.050 --> 40:47.285
It is my cousin Catherina
Sforza's doing.

40:47.386 --> 40:48.487
When?

40:48.588 --> 40:51.123
Tonight.
Now.

40:54.828 --> 40:56.095
<i>Get in there!</i>

40:57.665 --> 40:59.733
Do not leave
his side.

41:00.902 --> 41:03.204
Do not let anyone
else in.

41:06.275 --> 41:07.576
[door closes]

41:07.677 --> 41:14.316
[♪]

41:14.318 --> 41:21.757
[♪]

41:21.858 --> 41:23.659
[grunting]

41:29.165 --> 41:32.768
<i>[baby quietly crying]</i>

41:36.573 --> 41:38.207
[grunting]

41:42.145 --> 41:44.113
[grunting]

41:46.750 --> 41:48.317
Fuck!

41:54.257 --> 41:56.959
[grunting]

41:57.060 --> 41:59.228
[breathing heavily]

41:59.329 --> 42:00.496
[grunts]

42:02.098 --> 42:03.766
[loud clatter]

42:16.780 --> 42:18.948
[loud scream]

42:19.015 --> 42:20.048
[groan]

42:21.151 --> 42:23.018
CESARE:
Where are they?

42:23.086 --> 42:24.887
Your sister's bedroom.

42:28.358 --> 42:30.126
[door rattles]

42:33.897 --> 42:35.064
[relieved sigh]

42:35.165 --> 42:36.932
[baby cries]

42:37.000 --> 42:38.433
Shh...

42:39.535 --> 42:41.036
CESARE:
Thank God.

42:42.539 --> 42:43.906
Shhh...

42:45.075 --> 42:46.876
[breathing heavily]

42:46.977 --> 42:48.411
[baby cries]

42:48.478 --> 42:50.079
Shh...

42:53.250 --> 43:06.763
[♪]

43:06.765 --> 43:17.540
[♪]

43:22.012 --> 43:23.613
They were warned.

43:23.680 --> 43:25.314
Ascanio betrayed us.

43:25.382 --> 43:26.949
<i>[door closes]</i>

43:29.820 --> 43:31.621
[slams shut]

43:33.556 --> 43:35.624
Then we will have
to find another way.

43:35.725 --> 43:37.726
That will be difficult.

43:37.794 --> 43:39.628
They will be watching
for assassination.

43:39.729 --> 43:41.797
No.

43:41.898 --> 43:43.799
No more assassination.

43:49.004 --> 43:50.438
What then?

43:54.944 --> 43:56.911
Those they have
dispossessed...

43:58.480 --> 44:01.182
Those they have
made enemies of...

44:02.184 --> 44:03.551
Those upon whom

44:03.618 --> 44:05.453
they have trodden in
their ascent to power...

44:08.757 --> 44:10.624
Let us gather them to us.

44:12.327 --> 44:13.961
The cardinals?

44:14.029 --> 44:16.196
No.

44:16.264 --> 44:18.732
If our own cousin fails us,

44:18.799 --> 44:20.800
why look to the rest
of the Consistory?

44:23.537 --> 44:26.005
Go to their families.

44:26.073 --> 44:28.041
The young bloods,
blades for hire.

44:28.109 --> 44:32.612
Second sons.
Roberto and Paolo Orsini.

44:32.680 --> 44:35.181
Vitelezzo Vitelli.

44:35.249 --> 44:36.350
Prospero Colonna.

44:36.417 --> 44:38.319
Gian Paolo Baglioni.

44:38.386 --> 44:42.289
The families of Bologna,
Umbria, Siena.

44:43.491 --> 44:46.193
An alliance.

44:46.294 --> 44:48.995
You think they would fall in?

44:49.063 --> 44:51.565
For the most part
they hate each other.

44:51.632 --> 44:54.200
They hate the Borgias more.

44:54.302 --> 44:55.568
[snickers]

44:56.804 --> 44:58.438
Bring them to us.

44:58.506 --> 45:00.373
Marshal them under
our banner.

45:00.441 --> 45:02.742
And then let us
see where we stand.

45:13.286 --> 45:15.187
What's this?

45:17.757 --> 45:19.124
This is murder.

45:19.191 --> 45:21.793
MAN: Taken out of the
Borgia palace, so we heard.

45:21.861 --> 45:24.762
Run through and
through with swords.

45:24.830 --> 45:26.931
Seems there's
treason afoot.

45:26.999 --> 45:29.467
Best you keep
your eyes open.

45:32.070 --> 45:40.111
[choir singing throughout]

45:58.197 --> 45:59.764
Were you in time?

46:01.666 --> 46:03.301
Yes.

46:04.870 --> 46:06.203
[sighs]

46:07.539 --> 46:09.106
I thank God for it.

46:10.242 --> 46:13.511
Two men were
sent in the night

46:13.579 --> 46:16.647
to wipe my family from
the face of the earth

46:16.715 --> 46:19.116
and came within a blade's
breadth of doing so.

46:20.619 --> 46:23.120
The maid's family is dead.

46:23.188 --> 46:25.089
The maid too, I'm sure,
would have been disposed of

46:25.157 --> 46:26.958
had we not
finished her first.

46:27.025 --> 46:31.028
There is someone
thinking far ahead,

46:31.129 --> 46:32.396
tying up loose ends.

46:32.464 --> 46:34.232
Who?

46:34.333 --> 46:35.566
[choir finishes singing]

46:37.603 --> 46:39.937
<i>PRIEST:</i>
<i>Venite exultamus Domino...</i>

46:40.038 --> 46:42.206
<i>[priest continues]</i>

46:43.942 --> 46:46.743
His name is Rufio.

46:46.811 --> 46:51.314
He is a man of my cousin
Catherina Sforza's household.

46:51.381 --> 46:53.983
I have known him
since he was a boy.

46:54.051 --> 46:56.152
He's the most deadly,
the most lethal -

46:56.253 --> 46:57.486
We will find him.

46:57.554 --> 46:59.855
No, no, you will not.

46:59.957 --> 47:02.158
He's not a mere assassin.

47:02.226 --> 47:05.428
He has made himself a
student of the art of death.

47:05.529 --> 47:07.697
You will not find him
unless he wishes it.

47:09.934 --> 47:12.268
And so he
found you.

47:12.336 --> 47:16.139
He came to me and told me
to choose my allegiance.

47:16.240 --> 47:17.708
And you chose Rome.

47:17.776 --> 47:19.577
Yes, of course I chose Rome!

47:19.645 --> 47:21.879
What do you take me for?
A traitor?

47:21.947 --> 47:24.315
Why should I be
surprised at one more...

47:24.382 --> 47:27.517
...when there are so many?

47:27.618 --> 47:29.486
Where is Della Rovere?

47:32.290 --> 47:33.790
Gone.

47:33.858 --> 47:36.259
Who knows where.

47:36.327 --> 47:38.262
He had friends.

47:38.330 --> 47:40.597
Friends within
the Vatican.

47:40.665 --> 47:42.166
I knew nothing
of this.

47:42.233 --> 47:44.435
[scoffs]
I swear it.

47:44.536 --> 47:46.337
I knew nothing
before tonight.

47:49.008 --> 47:51.075
You did well enough.

48:03.522 --> 48:06.157
[birds cawing and chirping]

48:27.214 --> 48:29.816
[gasps]

48:38.325 --> 48:41.093
[bell tolling]
They came for our family?

48:42.162 --> 48:44.163
CESARE: [sighs]
It has passed.

48:44.231 --> 48:45.732
Everyone is well.

48:45.800 --> 48:47.267
Who was it?
Della Rovere?

48:47.368 --> 48:48.635
Perhaps.

48:48.702 --> 48:49.736
[scoffs]
Perhaps!

48:49.837 --> 48:51.404
More likely,

48:51.472 --> 48:54.741
this past night,
your poisoning

48:54.809 --> 48:56.743
has rattled the grass

48:56.811 --> 49:00.180
and all the snakes
in Rome have slid forth.

49:00.247 --> 49:02.349
Della Rovere may not
be the worst of it.

49:02.417 --> 49:03.817
Well, then who?
Who did it?

49:05.019 --> 49:07.521
Catherina Sforza.

49:13.462 --> 49:16.164
That bitch.

49:16.232 --> 49:17.599
[sighs]

49:17.667 --> 49:20.102
And you knew nothing of
this until it was upon us?

49:22.471 --> 49:24.940
Who is to protect
this family,

49:25.041 --> 49:26.741
if not you?

49:28.478 --> 49:29.711
Rodrigo!

49:29.779 --> 49:31.647
You are truly safe!

49:34.717 --> 49:36.184
And little Giovanni?

49:36.252 --> 49:37.985
He's safe.
I told you, Father.

49:38.053 --> 49:39.553
He's safe.
We're all safe.

49:39.655 --> 49:48.797
[♪]

49:48.799 --> 49:56.371
[♪]

49:56.438 --> 49:58.373
VANOZZA:
This night is done,

49:58.474 --> 50:00.308
it is daylight.

50:00.409 --> 50:02.276
Open your eyes.

50:02.344 --> 50:03.911
We're not safe.

50:03.979 --> 50:05.480
<i>ALEXANDER:</i>
<i>No.</i>

50:08.984 --> 50:10.818
We are at war.

